the spare room upstairs.

262
00:37:21,223 --> 00:37:22,432
That'd be so great.

263
00:37:24,267 --> 00:37:26,561
There is one other thing.

264
00:37:30,690 --> 00:37:32,025
Excuse me. Pardon me.

265
00:37:32,108 --> 00:37:33,944
(BICYCLE BELL RINGING)

266
00:37:34,027 --> 00:37:35,529
Coming through.

267
00:37:40,116 --> 00:37:42,077
Hey, pal. I got a
delivery on five.

268
00:37:42,911 --> 00:37:44,412
I don't think there's
anybody up there.

269
00:37:44,496 --> 00:37:45,997
Oh, man.

270
00:37:46,081 --> 00:37:48,416
I'm gonna catch hell if I don't collect.
You got to let me try.

271
00:37:50,919 --> 00:37:54,548
I'll tell you what. I got an extra medium.
Take it on the house.

272
00:38:01,429 --> 00:38:02,889
You are the man.

273
00:38:03,223 --> 00:38:04,683
God bless you, brother.

274
00:38:07,102 --> 00:38:08,270
All right.

275
00:38:23,577 --> 00:38:25,453
(MACHINE BEEPING)

276
00:39:05,994 --> 00:39:07,120
Okay.

277
00:40:20,610 --> 00:40:22,988
We're pretty well closed
here, folks. I'm sorry.

278
00:40:23,071 --> 00:40:25,532
Oh, come on, Stan.
It's Friday night.

279
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:28,410
Oh, kids.

280
00:40:28,827 --> 00:40:31,037
I got nothing but marinara now.

281
00:40:31,121 --> 00:40:33,164
Oh, I got to have
a Mister Pink, please.

282
00:40:33,248 --> 00:40:35,500
She worked through
dinner again, of course.

283
00:40:43,216 --> 00:40:44,342
Stan?

284
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:50,056
(LAUGHING) And he... I go, "So,
yeah, I mean, where were you?

285
00:40:50,140 --> 00:40:52,183
"I can't... I don't know
where you were, Cecil."

286
00:40:52,267 --> 00:40:54,769
And he goes,
"Not where you been at."

287
00:40:54,853 --> 00:40:58,606
I thought, "Oh, my God."
I just felt so awful.

288
00:41:23,673 --> 00:41:25,467
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

289
00:41:26,134 --> 00:41:27,552
(SOFTLY) Bruce?

290
00:41:34,142 --> 00:41:37,187
Betty? What's going on?

291
00:41:52,535 --> 00:41:53,661
Betty...

292
00:41:53,745 --> 00:41:56,831
Just tell me if I saw
what I think I saw.

293
00:41:58,124 --> 00:41:59,584
I don't know what to say.

294
00:41:59,709 --> 00:42:01,669
Please, just tell me the truth.

295
00:42:43,211 --> 00:42:45,839
Don't go.
Don't go.

296
00:42:46,756 --> 00:42:48,049
(SIGH ING)

297
00:42:55,682 --> 00:42:57,642
I want you to come with me now.

298
00:42:57,725 --> 00:42:59,936
Please. Come with me.

299
00:43:01,396 --> 00:43:02,605
Please.

300
00:43:18,997 --> 00:43:20,915
(GARAGE DOOR CLOSING)

301
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:34,262
BETTY: It's our data.

302
00:43:35,221 --> 00:43:38,266
I got in there before
they carted it all away.

303
00:43:40,476 --> 00:43:44,147
I hoped somewhere that it might
tell us something someday.

304
00:43:46,482 --> 00:43:48,151
Does the General know
that you have this?

305
00:43:48,234 --> 00:43:50,778
No, I don't think so.

306
00:43:51,237 --> 00:43:53,573
I haven't spoken to him
in a couple of years.

307
00:43:53,656 --> 00:43:55,158
You have to be sure.

308
00:43:55,241 --> 00:44:00,288
Bruce, I don't understand why we can't
just go in there together and talk to him.

309
00:44:00,371 --> 00:44:03,416
He told me what he wanted to do.

310
00:44:03,583 --> 00:44:05,335
He wants it out of me.

311
00:44:05,418 --> 00:44:08,671
He wants to dissect it
so that he can replicate it.

312
00:44:08,755 --> 00:44:10,965
He wants to make it a weapon.

313
00:44:57,887 --> 00:44:59,597
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

314
00:45:02,892 --> 00:45:04,185
Hi.
Hi.

315
00:45:05,353 --> 00:45:08,147
I thought you might want to...

316
00:45:08,231 --> 00:45:09,232
Thanks.

317
00:45:11,109 --> 00:45:14,696
Listen, I should leave early,
as early as I can.

318
00:45:14,779 --> 00:45:18,199
Really? You can't stay at all?

319
00:45:18,283 --> 00:45:21,619
I want to, but it's just not
safe for me to be here.

320
00:45:24,205 --> 00:45:26,958
If I could borrow some cash.
...Of course.

321
00:45:27,041 --> 00:45:28,626
I need to take a bus.

322
00:45:28,710 --> 00:45:31,421
Well, at least let me
walk you to the station.

323
00:45:33,381 --> 00:45:34,549
Okay.

324
00:45:38,344 --> 00:45:39,429
You have everything you need?

325
00:45:39,512 --> 00:45:40,513
Yeah.

326
00:45:44,058 --> 00:45:45,059
I...

327
00:45:46,519 --> 00:45:47,520
What?

328
00:45:49,981 --> 00:45:52,066
Good night.
Good night.

329
00:45:52,150 --> 00:45:54,152
I hope you get some rest.

330
00:46:36,277 --> 00:46:38,946
We're giving you
a very low dose only.

331
00:46:39,238 --> 00:46:41,866
I need you sharp
out there and disciplined.

332
00:46:41,949 --> 00:46:43,993
First sign of any side effect,

333
00:46:44,077 --> 00:46:47,789
we stop and you're off team
until you straighten out.

334
00:46:48,539 --> 00:46:49,624
Agreed?

335
00:46:49,707 --> 00:46:50,708
Agreed.

336
00:46:54,212 --> 00:46:56,964
You'll get two
separate infusions.

337
00:46:57,048 --> 00:47:01,219
One into the deep muscle, one
into the bone marrow centers.

338
00:47:01,302 --> 00:47:03,638
The bone ones are going to hurt.

339
00:47:18,694 --> 00:47:20,154
(GRUNTS)

340
00:47:50,268 --> 00:47:52,019
Is everything okay?

341
00:47:53,980 --> 00:47:55,356
I think so.

342
00:47:56,691 --> 00:47:58,484
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

343
00:48:03,739 --> 00:48:05,074
Come here.

344
00:48:05,450 --> 00:48:06,659
(CHUCKLES)

345
00:48:06,742 --> 00:48:07,827
I just wanna do this.

346
00:48:07,910 --> 00:48:08,911
Oh.

347
00:48:10,037 --> 00:48:11,122
It's better like that.

348
00:48:11,205 --> 00:48:12,206
Yeah?

349
00:48:16,878 --> 00:48:18,296
It feels too tight, huh?

350
00:48:18,379 --> 00:48:20,214
Yeah, a little.
Okay.

351
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:28,890
What?

352
00:48:29,765 --> 00:48:30,766
They're here.

353
00:48:31,017 --> 00:48:32,435
Betty, look at me, look at me!
Bruce!

354
00:48:32,518 --> 00:48:33,769
You have to go far away
from me as you can!

355
00:48:33,853 --> 00:48:35,354
Don't argue with me, just go.
Go! Bruce!

356
00:48:40,902 --> 00:48:42,695
(CAR ALARM BEEPING)

357
00:48:46,574 --> 00:48:48,659
Damn it! We'd have had snipers
on target in three more minutes.

358
00:48:48,743 --> 00:48:50,286
I wanna know who jumped the gun.

359
00:48:52,538 --> 00:48:53,748
He's heading 2-7-0.

360
00:49:10,932 --> 00:49:12,600
Blonsky! Not yet!

361
00:49:14,018 --> 00:49:15,186
Sir.

362
00:49:16,812 --> 00:49:18,439
Look alive.
This could get interesting.

363
00:49:52,932 --> 00:49:54,642
(BREATH ING DEEPLY)

364
00:50:06,654 --> 00:50:07,655
I got him!

365
00:50:07,822 --> 00:50:10,908
Stop! Stop!

366
00:50:12,743 --> 00:50:14,120
I know you're in there!

367
00:50:15,955 --> 00:50:17,582
General, please!

368
00:50:20,084 --> 00:50:21,127
Sir?

369
00:50:21,961 --> 00:50:23,004
Dad!

370
00:50:30,303 --> 00:50:32,263
Dad, please don't do this.

371
00:50:32,346 --> 00:50:34,432
You can't see this clearly.
Now, get inside.

372
00:50:34,515 --> 00:50:36,350
There he is!

373
00:50:36,434 --> 00:50:38,644
SOLDIER 1 ON RADIO: Target is in
the overpass. We have a visual.

374
00:50:38,728 --> 00:50:40,896
Do not engage!
Repeat, do not engage!

375
00:50:46,611 --> 00:50:48,195
SOLDIER 2:
He's locked in.

376
00:50:54,201 --> 00:50:55,703
Put two canisters
in there with him.

377
00:50:56,495 --> 00:50:57,538
Fire!

378
00:51:16,724 --> 00:51:17,725
Get her back here!

379
00:51:39,955 --> 00:51:41,499
(GROANING)

380
00:51:52,218 --> 00:51:53,260
Now she'll see.

381
00:51:54,428 --> 00:51:55,805
(ROARING)

382
00:52:16,117 --> 00:52:17,284
Alpha team?

383
00:52:19,245 --> 00:52:20,246
Let him have all of it.

384
00:52:26,585 --> 00:52:28,129
SOLDIER 2:
Come on, light him up!

385
00:52:31,340 --> 00:52:34,677
Where are the fifty cals?
Move your asses!

386
00:53:22,850 --> 00:53:24,059
Oh, my God!

387
00:53:27,688 --> 00:53:28,731
Blonsky, now you're up!

388
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:30,441
Sir?

389
00:53:31,734 --> 00:53:33,027
Cover me.

390
00:53:35,404 --> 00:53:36,655
(FIRES)

391
00:53:49,877 --> 00:53:51,045
(GROWLING)

392
00:53:51,128 --> 00:53:52,630
Remember me?

393
00:54:12,608 --> 00:54:14,026
My God, he's doing it.

394
00:54:19,073 --> 00:54:20,407
Move him toward the cannons!

395
00:54:26,539 --> 00:54:27,540
Move!

396
00:54:41,095 --> 00:54:42,346
SOLDIER 2:
Hold your position!

397
00:54:42,429 --> 00:54:43,764
Do it now!

398
00:54:54,692 --> 00:54:56,694
(HIGH-PITCHED BUZZING)

399
00:55:09,623 --> 00:55:11,166
Please, please, please, no!

400
00:55:11,250 --> 00:55:12,668
Please, please, please!
Get her back!

401
00:55:12,751 --> 00:55:13,794
You're killing him!

402
00:55:13,878 --> 00:55:16,213
Stop! Get off of me!

403
00:55:16,297 --> 00:55:17,715
(DISTORTED) Bruce!

404
00:55:20,801 --> 00:55:24,722
(DISTORTED)
Bruce! Bruce!

405
00:55:54,126 --> 00:55:55,169
Where's the gunship?

406
00:56:04,887 --> 00:56:06,180
(GROWLS)

407
00:56:15,356 --> 00:56:16,357
Is that it?

408
00:56:16,649 --> 00:56:18,400
Blonsky, pull back now.

409
00:56:18,484 --> 00:56:19,818
Pull back!

410
00:56:22,905 --> 00:56:24,698
Is that all you got?

411
00:56:32,247 --> 00:56:34,833
Fall back! SOLDIER 3: Fall back!
Let's go, let's go!

412
00:56:34,917 --> 00:56:36,293
GENERAL: Find cover!

413
00:56:40,339 --> 00:56:41,548
Betty!

414
00:56:55,020 --> 00:56:56,480
Fire, goddamn it!

415
00:56:58,273 --> 00:56:59,483
Bruce?

416
00:56:59,566 --> 00:57:01,026
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

417
00:57:12,663 --> 00:57:13,914
Stop firing!

418
00:57:27,428 --> 00:57:28,887
No!

419
00:58:18,979 --> 00:58:21,565
You did the right thing,
calling us.

420
00:58:23,650 --> 00:58:26,570
I need to know
where they're going.

421
00:58:26,653 --> 00:58:28,822
She'll be in incredible danger
as long as she's with him.

422
00:58:28,906 --> 00:58:30,199
From who?

423
00:58:31,116 --> 00:58:33,702
He protected her.
You almost killed her.

424
00:58:33,786 --> 00:58:37,581
I give you my word, her safety is
my main concern at this point.

425
00:58:37,664 --> 00:58:40,334
You know, it's a point
of professional pride with me

426
00:58:40,417 --> 00:58:43,337
that I can always tell
when somebody's lying.

427
00:58:43,670 --> 00:58:44,880
And you are.

428
00:58:46,048 --> 00:58:48,342
I don't know where he's going.

429
00:58:49,301 --> 00:58:50,969
I know she'll help him,
if she can.

430
00:58:51,053 --> 00:58:53,138
Then she's aiding a fugitive.

431
00:58:54,723 --> 00:58:57,309
And I can't help
either one of them.

432
00:59:02,356 --> 00:59:05,442
I used to wonder why she
never talked about you.

433
00:59:05,818 --> 00:59:07,194
Now I know!

434
00:59:12,116 --> 00:59:14,409
Where does she meet these guys?

435
00:59:19,540 --> 00:59:20,749
(SIREN WAILS)

436
00:59:53,240 --> 00:59:54,533
(SCREAMS)

437
00:59:55,534 --> 00:59:56,785
(GROANS)

438
01:00:03,917 --> 01:00:05,085
Bruce?

439
01:00:15,304 --> 01:00:16,513
Bruce.

440
01:00:25,063 --> 01:00:26,440
(ROARING)

441
01:00:36,658 --> 01:00:38,827
It's okay. It's okay.

442
01:00:51,965 --> 01:00:54,760
Come here.
Come this way.

443
01:00:57,971 --> 01:00:59,598
Watch your head.

444
01:01:14,655 --> 01:01:15,656
Okay.

445
01:01:26,625 --> 01:01:27,793
We're okay.

446
01:01:32,673 --> 01:01:34,049
It's okay.

447
01:01:35,884 --> 01:01:37,636
It's just the rain.

448
01:01:46,853 --> 01:01:49,106
GENERAL: Will he
ever walk again?

449
01:01:49,189 --> 01:01:52,734
Most of the bones in his body look
like crushed gravel right now.

450
01:01:52,818 --> 01:01:56,613
I will say this for him. He's
got a heart like a machine.

451
01:01:56,697 --> 01:01:59,908
Never seen anything like it,
outside of a racehorse.

452
01:03:02,512 --> 01:03:03,597
Here.

453
01:03:05,140 --> 01:03:06,141
Okay.

454
01:03:20,072 --> 01:03:21,615
(GROANS)

455
01:03:22,491 --> 01:03:23,992
(PANTING)

456
01:03:32,125 --> 01:03:33,877
(BRUCE VOMITING)

457
01:03:46,973 --> 01:03:48,183
Bruce?

458
01:03:49,726 --> 01:03:50,977
Oh, hi.

459
01:03:51,520 --> 01:03:52,646
Are you okay?

460
01:03:53,313 --> 01:03:54,314
Yeah.

461
01:03:54,648 --> 01:03:56,858
Yeah, actually,
I feel a lot better.

462
01:03:56,942 --> 01:03:59,528
Good. I just had to
get my data back.

463
01:04:01,113 --> 01:04:02,239
You ate it?

464
01:04:02,322 --> 01:04:06,535
Well, you know, the circumstances
called for a little improvisation.

465
01:04:06,618 --> 01:04:07,702
Wow.

466
01:04:09,204 --> 01:04:10,997
Okay, so they didn't
have a great selection,

467
01:04:11,081 --> 01:04:12,833
but I got you some options.

468
01:04:13,625 --> 01:04:16,169
First thing's first.

469
01:04:16,336 --> 01:04:17,963
(BETTY CHUCKLES)
BRUCE: Oh, you're kidding me.

470
01:04:28,181 --> 01:04:29,349
What?

471
01:04:29,808 --> 01:04:30,809
No.

472
01:04:30,892 --> 01:04:32,769
They were the stretchiest
pair they had.

473
01:04:32,853 --> 01:04:34,187
I'll take my chances.

