in the Smoky Mountain National Forest.

484
01:05:10,474 --> 01:05:12,476
Not too short back there.

485
01:05:12,559 --> 01:05:15,520
(CHUCKLES) I have done
this before, you know.

486
01:05:31,870 --> 01:05:34,456
I don't know how you've done this
on your own for all this time.

487
01:05:34,539 --> 01:05:36,458
With clippers, usually.

488
01:05:36,541 --> 01:05:38,001
(GIGGLING)

489
01:06:20,377 --> 01:06:21,962
(WATCH BEEPING)

490
01:06:26,299 --> 01:06:28,260
(WATCH BEEPING RAPIDLY)

491
01:06:31,304 --> 01:06:34,015
Wait, wait, wait. Wait.
What? What?

492
01:06:34,099 --> 01:06:35,433
We can't do this.

493
01:06:35,517 --> 01:06:37,644
It's okay. I want to.
No.

494
01:06:38,645 --> 01:06:39,646
No.

495
01:06:40,939 --> 01:06:42,190
I can't.

496
01:06:43,316 --> 01:06:45,193
(WATCH BEEPING SLOWS)

497
01:06:45,735 --> 01:06:47,737
I can't get too excited.

498
01:06:49,155 --> 01:06:50,365
(BEEPING STOPS)

499
01:06:50,448 --> 01:06:52,492
Not even a little excited?

500
01:06:52,576 --> 01:06:53,994
(SIGH ING)

501
01:06:55,203 --> 01:06:56,580
It's okay.

502
01:07:01,251 --> 01:07:03,128
Sir, it's Blonsky.

503
01:07:05,630 --> 01:07:08,550
Has anyone found out if he
has next of kin or family?

504
01:07:09,342 --> 01:07:11,011
Ask him yourself.

505
01:07:14,806 --> 01:07:15,849
Sir?

506
01:07:36,077 --> 01:07:38,204
Good to see you back
on your feet, soldier.

507
01:07:38,288 --> 01:07:39,289
Thank you, sir.

508
01:07:47,047 --> 01:07:48,298
How do you feel?

509
01:07:50,216 --> 01:07:52,677
Pissed off and ready
for round three.

510
01:07:59,100 --> 01:08:03,063
Basically, we can't use any of this,
because they can track all of it.

511
01:08:03,146 --> 01:08:05,982
Well, my lip gloss?
Can they track that?

512
01:08:06,941 --> 01:08:08,943
No. You can take
your lip gloss.

513
01:08:09,027 --> 01:08:10,028
Thank you.

514
01:08:10,111 --> 01:08:11,821
Well, I need my glasses.

515
01:08:12,030 --> 01:08:13,073
Well, you can take

516
01:08:13,114 --> 01:08:14,324
your glasses and your watch, okay?
Okay.

517
01:08:14,407 --> 01:08:17,994
We can use most of it. We just can't use
the credit cards, the ID or the phone.

518
01:08:18,078 --> 01:08:20,413
Don't even turn that on.
Okay.

519
01:08:20,538 --> 01:08:22,666
And we'll take
the cash, obviously.

520
01:08:22,749 --> 01:08:26,670
How will we get where we need to
go on $40 and no credit cards?

521
01:08:29,714 --> 01:08:32,550
Well, we could sell this.

522
01:08:32,634 --> 01:08:36,221
No. No, that's the only thing
you have left from her. No.

523
01:08:38,431 --> 01:08:41,142
Well, we'll have to
try and get it back.

