525
01:08:46,106 --> 01:08:48,358
and local PD have
been placed on alert.

526
01:08:48,441 --> 01:08:51,111
They'll pop up somewhere and when
they do, it comes straight to us.

527
01:08:51,194 --> 01:08:53,196
GENERAL: They're not
gonna just pop up.

528
01:08:53,279 --> 01:08:56,324
He made it five years and got across
borders without making any mistakes.

529
01:08:56,408 --> 01:08:58,243
He's not gonna use
a damn credit card now.

530
01:08:58,618 --> 01:09:00,370
If he was trying to escape,
he'd be long gone.

531
01:09:00,453 --> 01:09:01,663
He's not trying
to escape this time.

532
01:09:01,746 --> 01:09:04,207
He's looking for help and
that's how we're gonna get him.

533
01:09:04,290 --> 01:09:06,710
We know what they're after and we
know he's been talking to somebody.

534
01:09:06,793 --> 01:09:08,628
You all have copies
of the correspondence.

535
01:09:09,129 --> 01:09:11,214
The aliases
Mr. Green and Mr. Blue

536
01:09:11,297 --> 01:09:14,342
have been added to the
SHIELD Operations Database.

537
01:09:14,426 --> 01:09:17,303
If he comes up for air,
we'll be waiting.

538
01:09:17,387 --> 01:09:19,556
If he makes a peep,
we'll hear him.

539
01:09:19,639 --> 01:09:22,100
And when he slips up,
we'll be ready.

540
01:10:04,976 --> 01:10:05,977
Hey.

541
01:10:07,937 --> 01:10:09,147
Smile.

542
01:10:09,773 --> 01:10:10,774
(CAMERA BEEPS)

543
01:10:19,574 --> 01:10:21,201
What is it like?

544
01:10:23,161 --> 01:10:25,914
When it happens,
what do you experience?

545
01:10:26,664 --> 01:10:29,209
Remember those experiments
we volunteered for at Harvard?

546
01:10:29,292 --> 01:10:31,419
Those induced hallucinations?

547
01:10:32,170 --> 01:10:35,590
It's a lot like that, just a
thousand times amplified.

548
01:10:37,383 --> 01:10:41,304
It's like someone's poured
a liter of acid into my brain.

549
01:10:41,387 --> 01:10:43,306
Do you remember anything?

550
01:10:43,389 --> 01:10:46,142
Just fragments. Images.

551
01:10:46,726 --> 01:10:49,896
There's too much noise. I can
never derive anything out of it.

552
01:10:49,979 --> 01:10:52,106
But then it's still
you inside it.

553
01:10:52,190 --> 01:10:53,817
No. No, it's not.

554
01:10:56,027 --> 01:11:00,198
I don't know. In the cave, I
really felt like it knew me.

555
01:11:00,949 --> 01:11:02,325
Maybe your mind is in there,

556
01:11:02,408 --> 01:11:05,036
it's just overcharged and can't
process what's happening.

557
01:11:05,119 --> 01:11:08,456
I don't want to control it.
I want to get rid of it.

558
01:11:21,678 --> 01:11:23,137
Are you ready?

559
01:11:23,221 --> 01:11:24,973
Let's even the playing
field a little.

560
01:11:28,393 --> 01:11:29,686
Gentlemen.

561
01:11:33,606 --> 01:11:37,277
(CAR HON KING) BETTY: Bruce, wake up.
There's something going on.

562
01:11:48,413 --> 01:11:51,457
We got to go. Walk toward the back.
Just don't move too fast.

563
01:12:06,931 --> 01:12:08,558
MAN: All right. Come.

564
01:12:22,363 --> 01:12:23,948
BETTY: It is
a long way uptown.

565
01:12:24,032 --> 01:12:25,909
I think the subway's
probably quickest.

566
01:12:27,577 --> 01:12:29,454
Me in a metal tube,
deep underground,

567
01:12:29,537 --> 01:12:32,040
with hundreds of people in the
most aggressive city in the world?

568
01:12:32,123 --> 01:12:34,751
Right. Let's get a cab.

569
01:12:34,834 --> 01:12:39,088
CAB DRIVER: Come on, now! Let's go!
You're too slow! You drive like a woman!

570
01:12:39,172 --> 01:12:41,799
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING
ON RADIO)

571
01:12:44,010 --> 01:12:45,595
Very nice. You see her?
Oh, my.

572
01:12:45,678 --> 01:12:48,681
Very pretty.
Watch out, you goat!

573
01:12:48,848 --> 01:12:50,934
(WATCH BEEPING)
Breathe, breathe, breathe.

574
01:12:51,017 --> 01:12:52,769
(BRAKES SCREECH ING)

575
01:12:54,187 --> 01:12:56,856
Are you out of your mind?

576
01:12:56,940 --> 01:12:58,274
What is wrong with you?
What's the matter, baby?

577
01:12:58,358 --> 01:13:00,109
You don't like a good ride?

578
01:13:00,652 --> 01:13:01,819
(BETTY GROWLING)

579
01:13:01,903 --> 01:13:03,196
Asshole!

580
01:13:04,530 --> 01:13:06,240
(GRUNTS)

581
01:13:06,324 --> 01:13:08,785
You know, I know a few
techniques could help you

582
01:13:08,868 --> 01:13:10,620
manage that anger
very effectively.

583
01:13:10,703 --> 01:13:13,039
You zip it.
We're walking.

584
01:13:13,539 --> 01:13:14,582
Okay.

585
01:13:22,131 --> 01:13:24,008
BETTY: Excuse me.
Dr. Sterns?

586
01:13:24,133 --> 01:13:26,719
Yes. I'm sorry to bother you.
I'm Elizabeth Ross.

587
01:13:27,637 --> 01:13:29,639
Oh! Dr. Ross!

588
01:13:29,722 --> 01:13:31,474
I have someone
who'd like to meet you.

589
01:13:31,891 --> 01:13:32,892
Okay.

590
01:13:35,144 --> 01:13:36,562
It's Mr. Blue, isn't it?

591
01:13:38,439 --> 01:13:39,816
Mr. Green?

592
01:13:42,068 --> 01:13:45,697
I got to tell you, I've been
wondering if you were even real.

593
01:13:45,780 --> 01:13:47,532
And if you were,
what would it look like?

594
01:13:47,615 --> 01:13:52,328
A person with that much
power lurking in him.

595
01:13:52,412 --> 01:13:53,997
Nothing could have
surprised me more

596
01:13:54,080 --> 01:13:57,000
than this unassuming man
shaking my hand.

597
01:13:57,083 --> 01:13:59,711
But, look. We're not strolling
into the park for a picnic, here.

598
01:13:59,794 --> 01:14:01,504
Even if everything
goes perfectly,

599
01:14:01,587 --> 01:14:05,425
if we induce an episode, if we
get the dosage exactly right,

600
01:14:06,426 --> 01:14:08,344
is that going to be
a lasting cure

601
01:14:08,428 --> 01:14:11,764
or just some antidote to
suppress that specific flare-up?

602
01:14:11,973 --> 01:14:13,975
(SNAPPING FINGERS)

603
01:14:14,058 --> 01:14:15,518
I don't know.

604
01:14:16,269 --> 01:14:20,982
What I'm saying is that if we overshoot
this by even the smallest integer

605
01:14:21,941 --> 01:14:24,360
we're dealing
with concentrations

606
01:14:24,444 --> 01:14:26,821
with extraordinary
levels of toxicity.

607
01:14:26,904 --> 01:14:27,989
You mean it could kill him.

608
01:14:28,072 --> 01:14:29,449
Kill him? Yeah.

609
01:14:30,533 --> 01:14:31,534
I should say so.

610
01:14:33,161 --> 01:14:35,246
You should know that there's
a flip side to this, too.

611
01:14:35,329 --> 01:14:38,875
If we miss on the low side,
if we induce me and it fails,

612
01:14:38,958 --> 01:14:41,419
this will be
very dangerous for you.

613
01:14:41,502 --> 01:14:43,171
(CHUCKLES)

614
01:14:43,254 --> 01:14:47,258
Look. I've always been
more curious than cautious,

615
01:14:47,341 --> 01:14:49,135
and that's served me
pretty well.

616
01:14:50,136 --> 01:14:51,137
So, are we going to do this?

617
01:15:46,692 --> 01:15:48,319
How you feeling, man?

618
01:15:50,071 --> 01:15:51,656
Like a monster.

619
01:16:10,466 --> 01:16:11,467
(MACH IN ES WHIRRING)

620
01:16:11,551 --> 01:16:13,302
Okay. On the table.

621
01:16:14,053 --> 01:16:19,433
These will protect you from yourself
if you have a strong reaction.

622
01:16:20,685 --> 01:16:23,646
You can tell me later
if you thought it was strong.

623
01:16:27,859 --> 01:16:32,280
Oh, come on!
Stupid graduate students.

624
01:16:36,909 --> 01:16:37,910
Okay...

625
01:16:38,619 --> 01:16:40,079
You, you, you.

626
01:16:41,706 --> 01:16:45,168
This will be a somewhat
novel sensation.

627
01:16:47,795 --> 01:16:49,338
We have begun.

628
01:16:51,174 --> 01:16:54,177
The dialysis machine will mix
the antidote with your blood.

629
01:16:54,260 --> 01:16:58,723
Except the antidote will only take hold
once we've achieved a full reaction.

630
01:16:58,806 --> 01:17:00,016
Just relax.

631
01:17:00,766 --> 01:17:04,103
Okay. We are comprehensive.

632
01:17:07,315 --> 01:17:08,774
Here you go.

633
01:17:18,784 --> 01:17:20,786
All right.
We set to pop?

634
01:17:23,289 --> 01:17:25,458
I'd take your hands off him.

635
01:17:29,503 --> 01:17:31,422
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

636
01:17:45,269 --> 01:17:47,313
Oh, my God!

637
01:17:48,689 --> 01:17:50,233
(GRUNTING)

638
01:17:56,489 --> 01:17:57,990
(SCREAMING)

639
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:03,454
Wait, wait!
There's more! Wait!

640
01:18:14,257 --> 01:18:16,801
Now. Okay, now!
STERNS: Wait.

641
01:18:16,884 --> 01:18:19,512
Now, do it! Do it!

642
01:18:20,221 --> 01:18:21,555
(GRUNTS)

643
01:18:27,019 --> 01:18:29,522
Bruce! Bruce,
look at me.

644
01:18:29,605 --> 01:18:34,110
Stay with me. The antidote, now!
Sterns, do it now!

645
01:18:35,569 --> 01:18:39,490
Bruce, look at me. Look in my eyes.
Please, look in my eyes.

646
01:18:39,657 --> 01:18:42,076
(MACHINE BEEPING) Oh,
you've got to be kidding me!

647
01:18:52,837 --> 01:18:54,380
(GROANING)

648
01:19:02,805 --> 01:19:03,973
Bruce.

649
01:19:04,056 --> 01:19:05,474
Oh, my God.

650
01:19:16,861 --> 01:19:19,864
Bruce? Bruce,
can you hear me?

651
01:19:23,909 --> 01:19:25,077
Bruce?

652
01:19:33,919 --> 01:19:37,298
It's okay. You're okay.
You're okay.

653
01:19:40,718 --> 01:19:42,094
You did it.

654
01:19:42,261 --> 01:19:44,889
He's fine.
This is fantastic.

655
01:19:44,972 --> 01:19:46,349
BETTY: It's over.

656
01:19:47,266 --> 01:19:48,351
Hi.

657
01:19:48,684 --> 01:19:49,685
Hi.

658
01:19:56,609 --> 01:19:58,069
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

659
01:19:58,152 --> 01:20:04,116
That was the most extraordinary thing
I have seen in my entire life!

660
01:20:04,200 --> 01:20:05,743
Okay, you know what?
Stop, please.

661
01:20:05,826 --> 01:20:08,204
We need to go back and talk about
what just happened in there.

662
01:20:08,287 --> 01:20:12,083
Absolutely. Okay. The gamma
pulse came from the amygdala.

663
01:20:12,166 --> 01:20:13,918
I think Dr. Ross's primer...
Are you okay?

664
01:20:14,001 --> 01:20:17,254
...lets the cells absorb the energy
temporarily, and then it abates.

665
01:20:17,338 --> 01:20:20,174
That's why you didn't die of
radiation sickness years ago!

666
01:20:20,257 --> 01:20:22,968
Now, maybe we've neutralized
those cells permanently,

667
01:20:23,052 --> 01:20:24,929
or maybe we just
suppressed that event.

668
01:20:25,012 --> 01:20:27,390
I'm inclined to think the
latter, but it's hard to know

669
01:20:27,473 --> 01:20:29,225
because none of our test
subjects ever survived.

670
01:20:29,308 --> 01:20:30,976
Of course, they weren't getting
the primer! Wait, wait.

671
01:20:31,060 --> 01:20:32,478
Wait, what did you just say?
They weren't getting

672
01:20:32,561 --> 01:20:35,106
- the myostatin primer...
- No, no, no. Test subjects?

673
01:20:36,148 --> 01:20:37,900
What test subjects?

674
01:20:38,609 --> 01:20:39,652
Come with me.

675
01:20:40,236 --> 01:20:41,904
(SIRENS WAILING)

676
01:20:56,752 --> 01:20:57,878
What's the activity level?

677
01:20:57,962 --> 01:20:59,755
Snipers are covering
Alpha sector.

678
01:21:01,507 --> 01:21:02,925
STERNS ON RADIO:
We started on rats and mice,

679
01:21:03,008 --> 01:21:05,594
but it just completely fried
them, so we had to go bigger.

680
01:21:05,845 --> 01:21:08,931
And we still don't know which is
more toxic, the gamma or your blood.

681
01:21:09,014 --> 01:21:10,599
What do you mean, my blood?

682
01:21:11,100 --> 01:21:12,852
Bruce, this is all you.

683
01:21:13,644 --> 01:21:14,937
You didn't send me
much to work with,

684
01:21:15,020 --> 01:21:17,189
so I had to concentrate
it and make more.

685
01:21:17,731 --> 01:21:20,943
With a little more trial and error,
there's no end to what we can do!

686
01:21:21,026 --> 01:21:24,780
This is potentially Olympian!

687
01:21:24,864 --> 01:21:28,367
This gamma technology has
limitless applications.

688
01:21:28,451 --> 01:21:30,453
We'll unlock hundreds of cures.

689
01:21:30,536 --> 01:21:33,706
We will make humans
impervious to disease!

690
01:21:47,887 --> 01:21:49,555
No, no, we've got to destroy it.

691
01:21:50,014 --> 01:21:51,891
Wait, what?
All of it.

692
01:21:52,016 --> 01:21:53,350
Tonight. We're
gonna incinerate it.

693
01:21:53,434 --> 01:21:55,686
Is this the whole supply?
What...

694
01:21:55,769 --> 01:21:57,313
We could get the Nobel for this!

695
01:21:57,396 --> 01:21:59,648
You don't understand
the power of this thing.

696
01:21:59,732 --> 01:22:02,359
It is too dangerous.
It cannot be controlled.

697
01:22:03,068 --> 01:22:04,570
At your discretion, shooter.

698
01:22:04,612 --> 01:22:07,072
STERNS:... three of us! This is
Promethean fire! BRUCE: It's just...

699
01:22:07,156 --> 01:22:08,407
SOLDIER ON RADIO:
No shot.

700
01:22:11,911 --> 01:22:13,662
Blonsky's going in.

701
01:22:15,873 --> 01:22:18,751
GENERAL ON RADIO: Blonsky, stand down.
My daughter's in there!

702
01:22:21,337 --> 01:22:22,421
We have the antidote now.

703
01:22:22,505 --> 01:22:25,341
They don't want the antidote!
They want to make it a weapon!

704
01:22:27,510 --> 01:22:29,136
(SIRENS WAILING)

705
01:22:32,223 --> 01:22:34,266
And if we let it go,
we will never get it back.

706
01:22:34,433 --> 01:22:36,477
You don't know
how powerful this thing is.

707
01:22:36,560 --> 01:22:38,521
I hate the government
just as much as anyone,

708
01:22:38,604 --> 01:22:40,439
but you're being a little
paranoid, don't you think?

709
01:22:42,399 --> 01:22:44,360
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

710
01:22:44,443 --> 01:22:45,945
(SHRIEKS)

711
01:22:48,280 --> 01:22:49,782
Bruce! Bruce!

712
01:22:51,450 --> 01:22:52,701
BRUCE: Get out.

713
01:22:55,955 --> 01:22:58,707
Where is it? Come
on, where is it?

714
01:22:59,250 --> 01:23:00,584
(EXCLAIMS)

715
01:23:00,668 --> 01:23:02,878
(WATCH BEEPING RAPIDLY)

716
01:23:02,962 --> 01:23:04,588
Show him to me.

717
01:23:04,672 --> 01:23:06,048
(HEART BEATING SLOWLY)

718
01:23:06,131 --> 01:23:07,383
Blonsky!

719
01:23:15,849 --> 01:23:16,976
SOLDIER: Miss!

720
01:23:18,477 --> 01:23:19,812
Take this.

721
01:23:23,440 --> 01:23:24,733
If you took it from me,

722
01:23:24,817 --> 01:23:27,152
I'm gonna put you in a hole
for the rest of your life.

723
01:23:33,784 --> 01:23:34,994
Betty.

724
01:23:36,912 --> 01:23:39,915
I will never forgive
what you've done to him.

725
01:23:39,999 --> 01:23:41,333
He's a fugitive.

726
01:23:41,417 --> 01:23:43,377
You made him a fugitive

727
01:23:43,460 --> 01:23:46,964
to cover your failures
and to protect your career.

728
01:23:47,756 --> 01:23:50,593
Don't ever speak to me
as your daughter again.

729
01:23:52,845 --> 01:23:56,348
It's only because you're my daughter
that you're not in handcuffs, too.

730
01:24:00,603 --> 01:24:02,438
Are you telling me
you can make more like him?

731
01:24:02,521 --> 01:24:05,482
No! Not yet. I sorted
out a few pieces,

732
01:24:05,566 --> 01:24:08,777
but it's not like I can put
together the same Humpty Dumpty,

733
01:24:08,861 --> 01:24:10,738
if that's what you're asking.

734
01:24:10,821 --> 01:24:14,700
He was a freak accident!
The goal is to do it better!

735
01:24:14,783 --> 01:24:15,784
So Banner's the only...

736
01:24:15,868 --> 01:24:17,119
(THUDS)

737
01:24:20,497 --> 01:24:22,333
She's an annoying bitch.

738
01:24:22,625 --> 01:24:25,336
Why are you always
hitting people?

739
01:24:25,419 --> 01:24:27,296
(COCKING GUN)

740
01:24:27,379 --> 01:24:32,426
Now what possibly could I have
done to deserve such aggression?

741
01:24:32,509 --> 01:24:35,220
It's not what you've done.
It's what you're gonna do.

742
01:24:36,180 --> 01:24:38,641
I want what you got out of Banner.
I want that.

743
01:24:42,144 --> 01:24:46,231
You look like you've got a little
something in you already, don't you?

744
01:24:47,524 --> 01:24:51,153
I want more. You've seen
what he becomes, right?

745
01:24:51,904 --> 01:24:53,072
I have.

746
01:24:54,031 --> 01:24:55,574
And it's beautiful.

747
01:24:56,408 --> 01:24:57,660
Godlike.

748
01:24:57,910 --> 01:24:59,578
Well, I want that.

749
01:25:01,747 --> 01:25:03,832
I need that.
Make me that.

750
01:25:04,708 --> 01:25:07,711
I don't know what you've
got inside you already.

751
01:25:07,795 --> 01:25:09,421
The mix could be

752
01:25:10,005 --> 01:25:11,548
an abomination.

753
01:25:15,219 --> 01:25:18,097
I didn't say I was unwilling.

754
01:25:18,597 --> 01:25:22,351
I just need informed consent.

755
01:25:24,853 --> 01:25:26,647
And you've given it.

756
01:26:07,771 --> 01:26:11,942
This is what I was
trying to explain.

757
01:26:12,109 --> 01:26:17,030
(GROWLING) I don't know what
you've been ladling into yourself.

758
01:26:17,114 --> 01:26:19,199
But clearly it worked.

759
01:26:19,283 --> 01:26:22,911
Let's assume you don't
understand a word I'm saying,

760
01:26:22,995 --> 01:26:27,833
but if you'll just
get back on the table,

761
01:26:27,916 --> 01:26:30,419
I can fix this.

762
01:26:36,049 --> 01:26:38,010
(ABOMINATION LAUGHING)

763
01:26:45,309 --> 01:26:47,019
SOLDIER 1: Shoot it!
SOLDIER 2: Hey!

764
01:26:47,811 --> 01:26:48,812
No!

765
01:26:54,943 --> 01:26:56,528
(SCREAMING)

766
01:26:58,530 --> 01:27:00,532
Delta 4 to Leader.

767
01:27:00,616 --> 01:27:02,367
They took out two of our
guys, two of our guys!

768
01:27:02,451 --> 01:27:05,162
Blonsky and the Major
are still inside!

769
01:27:08,040 --> 01:27:10,334
Come on! Move,
move, move, move!

770
01:27:12,002 --> 01:27:13,879
(ABOMINATION GROWLING)

771
01:27:18,300 --> 01:27:19,885
It's over there!

772
01:27:21,678 --> 01:27:22,846
SOLDIER 2: Drop them!

773
01:27:22,888 --> 01:27:25,182
SOLDIER 3: What is that thing?
Shoot it!

774
01:27:26,725 --> 01:27:28,352
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

775
01:27:34,650 --> 01:27:38,445
Okay. All right! You... You, drive!
Let's go! Move, move!

776
01:27:38,529 --> 01:27:39,863
Delta 4 to Leader!
Go, go, go, go, go!

777
01:27:39,947 --> 01:27:41,907
Something big just
went off down here!

778
01:27:42,407 --> 01:27:44,493
General, you should hear this!

779
01:27:44,576 --> 01:27:47,538
The Hulk is in the street! I
repeat, the Hulk is in the street!

780
01:27:50,123 --> 01:27:52,167
That's impossible. You get a
hold of yourself, young man.

781
01:27:52,251 --> 01:27:54,253
You get it together.
What is your position?

782
01:27:54,461 --> 01:27:57,589
121st Street, heading
north on Broadway!

783
01:27:57,673 --> 01:27:59,258
Turn us around.

784
01:28:06,181 --> 01:28:09,351
We're going back.
Why are we going back?

785
01:28:09,434 --> 01:28:11,103
Damn it! Give me
eyes down there!

786
01:28:11,520 --> 01:28:12,813
Yes, sir!

787
01:28:14,815 --> 01:28:16,775
What the hell was that?

788
01:28:17,109 --> 01:28:18,694
Go, go, go!

789
01:28:34,459 --> 01:28:36,003
(SIREN WAILING)

790
01:28:42,301 --> 01:28:43,510
No!

791
01:28:48,765 --> 01:28:50,642
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

792
01:28:59,818 --> 01:29:01,153
One of yours?

793
01:29:01,361 --> 01:29:04,448
Oh, my God.
What have you done?

794
01:29:06,783 --> 01:29:08,619
OFFICER: Fire at him,
fire at him!

795
01:29:12,956 --> 01:29:15,042
Do you think a rifle's
gonna hurt that?

796
01:29:15,459 --> 01:29:16,710
Come on!

797
01:29:20,213 --> 01:29:21,381
Sweet.

798
01:29:21,882 --> 01:29:23,717
(ABOMINATION ROARING)

799
01:29:24,301 --> 01:29:25,510
Booyah!

800
01:29:30,641 --> 01:29:32,100
(LAUGHING)

801
01:29:40,192 --> 01:29:42,027
(CAR ALARM BEEPING)

802
01:29:43,528 --> 01:29:44,863
Get out of there, soldier!

803
01:29:48,200 --> 01:29:49,826
Stacy!

804
01:30:20,482 --> 01:30:22,401
Give me a real fight!

805
01:30:30,492 --> 01:30:31,660
SOLDIER 1: Sir?

806
01:30:34,329 --> 01:30:35,330
Sir?

807
01:30:36,999 --> 01:30:40,002
Tell them to bring everything
they've got and head for Harlem.

808
01:30:43,255 --> 01:30:44,756
It has to be me.

809
01:30:45,549 --> 01:30:47,092
You have to take me back there.

810
01:30:47,175 --> 01:30:48,760
What are you saying?

811
01:30:48,885 --> 01:30:50,178
You think you can control it?

812
01:30:50,262 --> 01:30:53,348
No, no, not control it, but,
I don't know, maybe aim it.

813
01:30:53,432 --> 01:30:54,933
And what if you can't?

814
01:30:56,476 --> 01:30:58,228
We made this thing.

815
01:30:58,729 --> 01:31:00,105
All of us.

816
01:31:01,064 --> 01:31:02,274
Please.

817
01:31:07,237 --> 01:31:09,740
Land us near it.
No, no. No, keep us high.

818
01:31:11,324 --> 01:31:12,659
Open the back door.

819
01:31:18,457 --> 01:31:23,295
Bruce! Bruce, stop!
Stop! What are you doing?

820
01:31:23,378 --> 01:31:27,132
Think about this! You don't
even know if you'll change!

821
01:31:29,134 --> 01:31:32,304
You don't have to do this!
Please, this is insane!

822
01:31:32,387 --> 01:31:34,139
Betty, I've got to try.

823
01:31:36,308 --> 01:31:37,642
I'm sorry.

824
01:32:00,332 --> 01:32:01,958
Oh, shit!

825
01:32:06,004 --> 01:32:07,255
Get her in here!

826
01:32:07,631 --> 01:32:08,632
Come on, miss.

827
01:32:26,233 --> 01:32:28,276
There. Betty!

828
01:32:29,528 --> 01:32:31,113
(MAN SCREAMING)

829
01:32:43,041 --> 01:32:44,709
(ROARING)

830
01:32:47,295 --> 01:32:48,713
Hulk!

831
01:32:53,635 --> 01:32:55,387
Yeah!

832
01:33:16,867 --> 01:33:18,702
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

833
01:33:21,121 --> 01:33:22,914
(CAR ALARM BEEPING)

834
01:33:37,262 --> 01:33:38,763
(LAUGHING)

835
01:33:39,598 --> 01:33:40,891
Come on!

836
01:33:42,225 --> 01:33:44,186
(CHATTERING ON RADIO)

837
01:34:13,131 --> 01:34:15,050
Is that all you've got?

838
01:34:28,813 --> 01:34:31,566
Use that thing, soldier!
Give him some help!

839
01:34:31,650 --> 01:34:32,901
Which one?

840
01:34:32,984 --> 01:34:35,320
Help the green one, damn it!
Which one do you think?

841
01:34:35,403 --> 01:34:37,280
Cut the other one in half!

842
01:34:39,950 --> 01:34:41,076
Ross!

843
01:35:05,850 --> 01:35:07,644
Keep it on him!

844
01:35:35,839 --> 01:35:38,800
Look, I got to put it down!
Hang on!

845
01:35:38,883 --> 01:35:39,926
(ALARM BEEPING)

846
01:36:46,076 --> 01:36:47,160
BETTY: Dad?

847
01:36:49,788 --> 01:36:52,290
(GROANING) Are you hurt?
Let me help you.

848
01:37:00,090 --> 01:37:02,550
I'm all right.
Just find a way out.

849
01:37:15,522 --> 01:37:16,815
(LAUGHS)

850
01:37:49,806 --> 01:37:52,642
You don't deserve this power!

851
01:37:53,226 --> 01:37:55,812
Now watch her die!

852
01:38:47,155 --> 01:38:48,823
Look out!

853
01:39:19,646 --> 01:39:20,939
General?

854
01:39:27,153 --> 01:39:29,781
Any last words?

855
01:39:32,575 --> 01:39:35,954
Hulk smash!

856
01:40:03,940 --> 01:40:05,441
(SCREAMS)

857
01:40:21,666 --> 01:40:23,418
(ROARING)

858
01:40:23,501 --> 01:40:25,128
BETTY: Stop!

859
01:40:55,533 --> 01:40:57,493
(ROARING)

860
01:41:45,833 --> 01:41:47,210
It's okay.

861
01:41:57,303 --> 01:41:58,971
Betty.

862
01:42:45,351 --> 01:42:47,311
(SEAGULLS SQUAWKING)

863
01:42:49,188 --> 01:42:50,898
(CAMERA BEEPS)

864
01:44:01,219 --> 01:44:02,845
(HEART BEATING)

865
01:44:12,814 --> 01:44:14,732
(HEART BEATING RAPIDLY)

866
01:44:26,994 --> 01:44:28,329
GENERAL: Reload.

867
01:44:34,293 --> 01:44:35,795
(GROANS)

868
01:44:35,878 --> 01:44:37,088
Reload.

869
01:44:53,104 --> 01:44:56,274
TONY: The smell of stale
beer and defeat.

870
01:44:56,357 --> 01:44:58,109
You know, I hate to say,
"I told you so," General,

871
01:44:58,192 --> 01:45:02,613
but that Super Soldier program
was put on ice for a reason.

872
01:45:02,697 --> 01:45:05,616
I've always felt hardware
was more reliable.

873
01:45:05,783 --> 01:45:07,118
Stark.

874
01:45:07,285 --> 01:45:08,286
General.

875
01:45:10,413 --> 01:45:12,915
You always wear such nice suits.

876
01:45:13,875 --> 01:45:15,209
Touché.

877
01:45:16,127 --> 01:45:17,920
I hear you have
an unusual problem.

878
01:45:18,004 --> 01:45:19,839
You should talk.

879
01:45:19,922 --> 01:45:21,424
You should listen.

880
01:45:24,135 --> 01:45:27,597
What if I told you we were
putting a team together?

881
01:45:27,680 --> 01:45:29,265
Who's "we"?

